# rio-build known-flakes — committed, coordinator-managed.
# Each row: {"test","symptom","root_cause","fix_owner":"P<N>","fix_description","retry"}
# Seeded 2026-03-18 from phase 2a-4a VM test history. P0202 exit: ".#ci green at >99%" — this table covers the residual <1%.
# Match key is `test` (exact); `symptom` is the grep-able CI log signature for human cross-check.
{"test": "vm-lifecycle-core-k3s", "drv_name": "rio-lifecycle-core", "symptom": "loadFlannelSubnetEnv failed: open /run/flannel/subnet.env: no such file or directory", "root_cause": "k3s flannel CNI race: pods scheduled before flannel control loop writes subnet.env. Usually self-heals via kubelet retry; occasionally stalls long enough that agent node never registers. Platform flake \u2014 not a rio-build bug.", "fix_owner": "P0179", "fix_description": "P0179's server-node-exists gate (b42a0af) + 600s budget (7c437e1) absorbs most occurrences by giving flannel init time. DISTINCT from airgap-timing (no loadFlannelSubnetEnv in log = wrong-gate bug, not this). [x2] prefix = nixbuild already retried once; one more local retry is the cap.", "retry": "Once"}
{"test": "vm-lifecycle-autoscale-k3s", "drv_name": "rio-lifecycle-autoscale", "symptom": "nodes \"k3s-agent\" not found \u2014 waitReady timeout at server-node gate, NO loadFlannelSubnetEnv in log", "root_cause": "Builder variance on airgap import. k3s imports images serially/alphabetically before kubelet starts; rio-controller\u2192gateway\u2192scheduler\u2192store\u2192worker at ~25s/image typical, but 5\u00d7 slower builders observed (7c437e1). autoscale is the longest critical-path fragment (~14min) \u2192 most susceptible to tail variance blowing the 600s gate.", "fix_owner": "P0179", "fix_description": "P0179 bumped gate 300s\u2192600s (7c437e1) tuned on observed tail (~170s agent import). If a >6\u00d7 slow builder shows up, gate blows \u2014 RERUN gets a different builder allocation. Structural fix would need a larger budget OR per-builder scaling, neither planned.", "retry": "Once"}
{"test": "vm-lifecycle-recovery-k3s", "drv_name": "rio-lifecycle-recovery", "symptom": "recovery subtest timeout \u2014 sched_metric_wait exceeds 120s default on settle or dispatch", "root_cause": "Flannel-race cascade into subtest timing. Bootstrap self-heals but delayed pod startup enough that subsequent subtests miss budget. Also: recovery kills scheduler leader \u2192 new leader's recover_from_pg takes ~15-30s under coverage instrumentation; timing-sensitive.", "fix_owner": "P0176", "fix_description": "P0176 switched metric scrapes to apiserver pods/proxy (97f1305, no port-forward TIME_WAIT cascade) and bumped sched_metric_wait 60\u2192120s (245a351). Retry cost ~200ms/attempt now vs ~3-5s before \u2014 variance was pf-induced, not application-induced. If this blows, it's a genuinely slow builder.", "retry": "Once"}
{"test": "vm-le-stability-k3s", "drv_name": "rio-leader-election-stability", "symptom": "loadFlannelSubnetEnv failed OR nodes k3s-agent not found at bootstrap", "root_cause": "k3s flannel subnet race / airgap import builder variance at bootstrap. No leader-election-specific flake mode remains after P0176's failover-wait relaxation (7763b00: standby-wins is a fair race post-step_down; tx+1 is the sole invariant).", "fix_owner": "P0179", "fix_description": "P0179's server-node-exists gate + 600s airgap budget covers the bootstrap surface. The standby-wins assertion was structurally relaxed in 7763b00 (P0176) \u2014 if `new_leader == standby` fails, that's a regression of 7763b00, not a retry case.", "retry": "Once"}
{"test": "vm-le-build-k3s", "drv_name": "rio-leader-election-build", "symptom": "build-during-failover dispatch wait timeout \u2014 derivations_running stays 0 beyond 120s after leader kill", "root_cause": "Build-during-failover timing. Leader kill \u2192 step_down \u2192 fair race (standby 5s poll vs replacement ~3-5s cold-start). New leader's first dispatch Tick is 10s cadence; under TCG + coverage instrumentation, new-leader-ready to first-dispatch can exceed budget. kubectl-logs-grep was the OLD dispatch check \u2014 FIXED in P0176/P0179; now uses metrics.", "fix_owner": "P0176", "fix_description": "P0176 switched dispatch check to scheduler metrics via pods/proxy (095b94a\u219297f1305) \u2014 kubelet http2 log-stream fragility no longer in the path. P0179 (96763b0) dropped log-grep entirely for cgroup state. If metrics-based check times out, it's genuine dispatch lag under TCG, not observation fragility.", "retry": "Once"}
{"test": "vm-cli-k3s", "drv_name": "rio-cli", "symptom": "loadFlannelSubnetEnv failed OR nodes k3s-agent not found at bootstrap", "root_cause": "k3s flannel/airgap bootstrap variance. cli scenario has no timing-sensitive subtests of its own \u2014 failures are always at the k3s-full fixture bootstrap. Coverage profraw collection race (7fd2f95) is a .#coverage-full issue, not .#ci.", "fix_owner": "P0179", "fix_description": "P0179's bootstrap gate covers this. cli-k3s is the shortest k3s test; least susceptible but shares the bootstrap surface. If this flakes while other k3s tests pass in the same .#ci run, it's builder allocation luck \u2014 RERUN.", "retry": "Once"}
